5:
Phew! That was some SERIOUSLY
quick thinking there, using the
flowers to cushion her fall! Good job!
9:
I-it was nothing. I hardly had any
time to think, I just acted on instinct.
14: I... um... My name is Echo.
19:
I'm terribly sorry for causing you so
much trouble!
23:
Trouble? Don't be silly, it wasn't any
trouble at all.
26:
No, it's true. My own carelessness
brought this about. I can't believe
you even went out of your way to
give me a medical check-up too...
31:
Don't be so hard on yourself, Echo.
You're safe now, aren't you?
35:
Yep, it's all good! You don't have a
single scratch on you! We're just
happy to have met you!
39:
I... R-really? B-but I haven't... done
anything...
44:
Oh, we caught your camera too! Do
you want to give it a look over and
see if it's still working?
52:
Lady Primula! Lady Pythica! I highly
recommend you soak in the sights
upon the observation deck!
57:
I was doing just that when I spied
you two down below, whereby I
made this most prompt descent!
66:
Hey, did you two get a look at the
lighthouse already? The view is
sweet as hell—
70:
Wh-whoa. Who the heck is that
cutie?! Is she from this Float?
78:
STOP right there! Give the poor girl a
break, already! She's been through
enough!
83:
Don't worry about those two, Echo.
They're both a little odd, but they're
good people deep down.
88:
What's that supposed to mean?
You're gonna ruin my first
impression here!
93:
Fear not, for I truly AM good; such is
necessarily the way of those who
walk the path of a ninja samurai!
98:
Just... keep your loincloth covered
up, okay?!
102:
I, I'm so sorry! I was just testing to
see if the camera still worked!
105:
And you all just... looked like you
were having so much fun, I couldn't
help myself.
110:
Haha! Look at me, my mouth's wide
open!
114:
Is... that really how I look when I
laugh? Goodness.
123:
Oh, I'm sorry! Th-this is part of my
power! It's not dangerous at all, so
please don't worry.
126:
This just kind of happens whenever I
get excited or happy.
130:
You mean... my photo made you
happy?
133:
Y-yes. Very. That's why the flower
went and bloomed.
141:
Um, that makes me happy too.
Thank you!
146:
Hehe. Echo, you've got a knack for
capturing people's smiles! Look at
us all, pearly whites on display!
150:
N-no, I'm really nothing special.
Besides, lately I've been taking
nothing but landscape shots.
154:
Actually, what I really wanted to
photograph today was...
159:
Echo, are you okay? Are you sure
this is safe?
162:
Should I go ahead and lay down
some flowers ahead of time? Just in
case?
165:
We should be able to catch her
even if she falls. Still though, she's
got some serious guts.
170:
There's a place on this island that's...
very important to me.
173:
But you can't get there anymore... 
I'm afraid I might lose it forever.
177:
Oh, would that be because of the
redevelopment of the island?
180:
Yes. That's why I came out here... I
figured I might be able to get a
good shot of it, even if it's from afar.
190:
Looks like we've got no other choice
but to go there for ourselves!
203:
It's just... My family are the ones who
are spearheading the
redevelopment. My father
specifically warned me not to go
there.
208:
Family, huh? Sounds to me like you'd
be authorized to enter that area,
then! No foul play by my books!
221:
Calamitous woe be to any obstacle
that stands in the way of this
maiden fair!
225: Um. I'm not sure that was necessary.
229: Wh-what? But Lady Parfait said that—
233:
I was saying that we could just have
Shota levitate us over the fence...
238:
Oh... The thought did not occur to
me!
243:
Well, whatever. It's busted now. If
someone comes complaining,
Zantetsu can pay for it out of his
own pocket.
248: All right then, let's go! Come on, Echo!
258:
Alk, do you have a moment? My
partner's dug up something
interesting.
260:
The redevelopment plan here...
Looks like there might be more to it
than meets the eye. Could even be
a bit of fun for us.
